PN,36901
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,FThe "devastated" foster parents of a
OL,7,F13-month-old baby boy murdered by a
OL,8,Fman who adopted him say they are now
OL,9,F"mistrustful and anxious" about
OL,10,Fchildren leaving their care to live
OL,11,Fwith strangers.
OL,13,FSandra and Paul Cooper looked after
OL,14,FPreston Davey from when he was five-
OL,15,Fdays-old until he was almost 10-months
OL,16,Fwhen he left them to live with his
OL,17,Fadoptive parents, teacher Jamie
OL,18,FVarley, and his partner John McGowan-
OL,19,FFazakerley in Blackpool.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,FThe Coopers said Preston was due to be
OL,7,Fthe last child they fostered but they
OL,8,Fnow feel they could not retire after
OL,9,Fhe died.
OL,11,FReading out a victim impact statement
OL,12,Fduring Varley and McGowan-Fazakerley's
OL,13,Fsentencing at Preston Crown Court,
OL,14,FSandra Cooper said: "We felt we had a
OL,15,Fduty to other children and could not
OL,16,Fsit back and enjoy ourselves knowing
OL,17,Fthat other children were being abused,
OL,18,Fmistreated and could die.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,F"My husband Paul and I have continued
OL,7,Fto foster children to protect them. We
OL,8,Fare doing this for Preston, in his
OL,9,Fmemory.
OL,11,F"Paul and I have previously felt that
OL,12,Fthe best option for all our foster
OL,13,Fchildren was to leave us happy and
OL,14,Fhealthy to go and live with a new
OL,15,Fpermanent adoptive family.
OL,17,F"We now struggle with this, and I will
OL,18,Ffeel mistrustful and anxious about any
OL,19,Fof our children leaving our care to
OL,20,Flive with strangers.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,F"Paul and I will often watch the
OL,7,Fvideos we took of Preston when he was
OL,8,Fhappy with us laughing and giggling,
OL,9,Fplaying with his toys smiling.
OL,11,F"Preston's face would light up when we
OL,12,Flooked at him; he was joyful, so
OL,13,Fcontent and happy, with sparkly
OL,14,Fsmiling eyes. That is how we want to
OL,15,Fremember him.
OL,17,F"I will often dream about Preston and
OL,18,FI feel that he is still alive, but
OL,19,Fwhen I wake up I realise he has died
OL,20,Fand I go through the trauma again of
OL,21,Fknowing he has died and how."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,FPreston's foster dad Paul Cooper said
OL,7,Fhe wakes up three to four times a
OL,8,Fnight thinking about Preston.
OL,10,FIn his victim statement he said:
OL,11,F"Preston was an absolute pleasure to
OL,12,Flook after, he was the most amazing
OL,13,Flittle boy who lit up the room as you
OL,14,Fwalked into it."
OL,16,FHe told the court saying goodbye to
OL,17,FPreston and handing him over to Varley
OL,18,Fand McGowan-Fazakerley was extremely
OL,19,Fdifficult.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,F"There hasn't been a day go by that I
OL,7,Fhaven't thought about Preston and what
OL,8,Fhe went through. I just wish we could
OL,9,Fhave kept him," he added.
OL,11,F"I think about the world and the
OL,12,Fpeople out there and if these so
OL,13,Fcalled 'respectable' person/s can do
OL,14,Fthis then anyone could - I do not
OL,15,Ftrust anybody anymore.
OL,17,F"As a foster carer you have to put so
OL,18,Fmuch trust in the system and the
OL,19,Fpersons responsible for caring for a
OL,20,Fchild.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,F"What happened to Preston has caused
OL,7,Fme to lose that trust, thus affecting
OL,8,Fme socially and throughJbeing a foster
OL,9,Fcarer.
OL,11,F"I don't see being a Foster Carer as
OL,12,Fan 'employment' more like a vocation.
OL,13,FPreston had his whole life ahead of
OL,14,Fhim, one that should have been a happy
OL,15,Flife with a new family. "
OL,17,FPreston had been taken from his
OL,18,Fbiological mother, Sarah Davey, now
OL,19,F42, by an emergency care order by
OL,20,FOldham Council.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,FAt 14, Ms Davey was jailed for the
OL,7,F"unspeakably wicked" murder of a frail
OL,8,Fpensioner in 1998 and has been in and
OL,9,Fout of prison since then.
OL,11,FIn her victim impact statement, Ms
OL,12,FDavey described the day Preston was
OL,13,Ftaken from her as one of the worst of
OL,14,Fher life.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,FShe said: "I had no choice in that
OL,7,Fdecision. I tried to take some comfort
OL,8,Fin believing he would be safe, loved,
OL,9,Fand protected, and he was with his
OL,10,Ffoster parents, Sandra and Paul
OL,11,F(Cooper), I trusted them, they and the
OL,12,Fsystem trusted you, that trust was
OL,13,Fcompletely and unforgivably broken.
OL,15,F"Every single day, I live with the
OL,16,Funimaginable pain of wondering what he
OL,17,Fwent through.
OL,26,@nD@KOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,F"Those thoughts do not leave me. They
OL,7,Fare with me when I wake up, and they
OL,8,Fhaunt me when I try to sleep. The
OL,9,Freality of how he suffered is
OL,10,Fsomething I will carry for the rest of
OL,11,Fmy life."
OL,13,FChildren's Commissioner Dame Rachel De
OL,14,FSouza said the murder of 13-month-old
OL,15,FPreston Davey was a "massive
OL,16,Fsafeguarding failure" and she will
OL,17,Fpursue the question of whether it was
OL,18,Fpreventable with "that baby's broken
OL,19,Fbody at the front of my mind".
OL,26,@sD@IO]wD@UOUxD@UO]zD@ROU{D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,FSpeaking on BBC Radio 4's Today
OL,7,Fprogramme before the sentencing of
OL,8,FPreston's adoptive parents Jamie
OL,9,FVarley and John McGowan-Fazakerley,
OL,10,Fshe said: "What do we know about
OL,11,FPreston?
OL,13,F"We know that very early into his
OL,14,Fadoption, and he was only an adoption
OL,15,Fwith his family for four months, very
OL,16,Fearly, he was taken to hospital with
OL,17,Fbruises.
OL,19,F"The consultant dismissed it. Did they
OL,20,Fdismiss it because it was a teacher
OL,21,Fadopter?
OL,26,@rD@KOUuD@AOU{D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36912
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781857088
OL,3,CFoster parents of murdered baby 'no
OL,4,Clonger trust anybody'
OL,6,F"Did that evil abuser hoodwink people
OL,7,Funder that professional guise?
OL,9,F"The social worker saw him 20 days
OL,10,Fbefore he died, I want to know whether
OL,11,Fthe correct level of professional
OL,12,Fcuriosity was there.
OL,14,F"I have huge numbers of questions, and
OL,15,FI'm not going to let go until I have
OL,16,Fthe answers."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUvD@AOUxD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/12
